1
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:54,720
F-F...

2
00:01:57,180 --> 00:01:57,970
F...

3
00:01:58,680 --> 00:02:01,230
Frog!

4
00:02:02,310 --> 00:02:05,560
Don't "ribbit" me, you dumb frog!

5
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:09,530
You derailed the train
with your sumo slap!

6
00:02:10,940 --> 00:02:12,110
Get outta the way, frog!

7
00:02:12,110 --> 00:02:13,860
We're gonna crash!

8
00:02:15,370 --> 00:02:18,450
And we'd almost caught up
to Sanji and the others!

9
00:02:18,450 --> 00:02:20,200
What're you gonna do about it?!

10
00:02:22,370 --> 00:02:24,120
That does it!

11
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:27,380
I'm gonna eat you, you jerk!

12
00:02:32,670 --> 00:02:34,340
Ow, ow, ow...

13
00:02:34,340 --> 00:02:37,260
What in the world is going on
with this sea train?

14
00:02:37,260 --> 00:02:39,100
Hey, you all okay?

15
00:02:42,430 --> 00:02:44,440
I guess.

16
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:44,440
Ow, ow...

17
00:02:44,440 --> 00:02:46,560
M-My back...!

18
00:02:51,110 --> 00:02:52,650
What the hell?!

19
00:02:53,030 --> 00:02:55,320
Our king bulls disappeared!

20
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:56,450
– What?!
– What?!

21
00:02:56,450 --> 00:02:58,370
– Whaddya mean, they disappeared?!
– Whaddya mean, they disappeared?!

22
00:02:58,370 --> 00:03:00,870
Well, it's more like we disappeared.

23
00:03:00,870 --> 00:03:03,410
I bet we got derailed.

24
00:03:03,410 --> 00:03:05,710
– Whoa! That's even worse!
– Whoa! That's even worse!

25
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:06,790
What do we do?!

26
00:03:06,790 --> 00:03:08,000
Hey!

27
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:08,750
Huh?

28
00:03:09,460 --> 00:03:11,460
How're we doing up there?!

29
00:03:11,460 --> 00:03:15,470
We'll still make it to Enies Lobby, right?

30
00:03:15,470 --> 00:03:19,140
Shut your damn pie hole and wait!

31
00:03:19,510 --> 00:03:24,230
That being said, we're caught
in a strange sea current.

32
00:03:24,230 --> 00:03:25,890
What's going on?

33
00:03:25,890 --> 00:03:26,730
Miss Kokoro.

34
00:03:26,730 --> 00:03:27,480
Huh?

35
00:03:27,850 --> 00:03:29,900
Do you still know the island's direction?

36
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:30,650
Yeah.

37
00:03:30,650 --> 00:03:36,990
The sea train comes equipped with eternal poses
for any island with a train station.

38
00:03:37,450 --> 00:03:38,700
Then we're fine!

39
00:03:38,700 --> 00:03:40,990
I'll watch the sea, so you steer the train!

40
00:03:40,990 --> 00:03:41,870
Hm?

41
00:03:41,870 --> 00:03:43,330
What're you gonna...?

42
00:03:43,330 --> 00:03:44,910
Me?

43
00:03:44,910 --> 00:03:46,080
I'm a navigator!

44
00:03:46,410 --> 00:03:47,580
Oh, I see!

45
00:03:47,580 --> 00:03:50,080
That's reassuring!

46
00:03:52,210 --> 00:03:54,090
Oh, before that...

47
00:03:54,670 --> 00:03:56,800
Hey, Yokozuna!

48
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:58,590
Come here a moment!

49
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:07,640
What a jump!

50
00:04:12,770 --> 00:04:15,740
So you're glad we're okay?!

51
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:16,860
Oh, please...

52
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:20,360
It's not like I was kidnapped or anything!

53
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,870
You jumped the gun.

54
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:28,000
Grandma can talk to Yokozuna?

55
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,670
What're you guys up to?

56
00:04:34,670 --> 00:04:37,880
The old lady's talking with
that frog from earlier.

57
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:40,680
What?! So she's really a frog?!

58
00:04:40,680 --> 00:04:43,680
She does seem to be more frog than human...

59
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:46,220
She's gonna kick your ass later.

60
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:47,230
No doubt.

61
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,020
Hey!

62
00:04:49,020 --> 00:04:51,230
Mr. Straw Hat! Rocketman!

63
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,810
Do you see them?!

64
00:04:52,810 --> 00:04:54,320
No, I don't!

65
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:57,440
Damn that overgrown frog!

66
00:04:57,440 --> 00:05:00,070
Where did he send
Straw Hat and the others flying?!

67
00:05:00,070 --> 00:05:01,070
Guys!

68
00:05:01,070 --> 00:05:02,660
Quit your bellyaching!

69
00:05:03,030 --> 00:05:06,740
We set out to sea to rescue Big Bro Franky!

70
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:07,790
That's right!

71
00:05:07,790 --> 00:05:13,540
While we hold out for Rocketman's return,
we need to continue on to Enies Lobby!

72
00:05:13,540 --> 00:05:16,340
Keep it up, Sodom and Gomorrah!

73
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,510
Huh?!

74
00:05:21,510 --> 00:05:23,800
Hey, guys! Up ahead!

75
00:05:24,390 --> 00:05:27,810
I've found more detached cars!

76
00:05:28,350 --> 00:05:30,270
They could be friend or foe!

77
00:05:30,270 --> 00:05:31,980
Everyone, get ready to fight!

78
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:35,480
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

79
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,730
Ahoy!

80
00:05:36,730 --> 00:05:38,900
Is anyone in there?!

81
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:40,530
We're the Franky Family!

82
00:05:40,530 --> 00:05:42,410
Show yourself!

83
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:45,320
Hey, someone came out!

84
00:05:49,830 --> 00:05:51,410
H-He's alive?!

85
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:55,130
Is... Is that true?!

86
00:05:55,590 --> 00:05:58,590
Yes... so I was told.

87
00:05:59,510 --> 00:06:00,970
I see...

88
00:06:02,090 --> 00:06:03,760
I see...

89
00:06:04,180 --> 00:06:05,680
Stupid old Dumburg!

90
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,720
I thought he'd been done in!

91
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:08,970
He's really...

92
00:06:08,970 --> 00:06:10,060
Thank goodness.

93
00:06:10,060 --> 00:06:14,230
CP9 probably believes they killed him.

94
00:06:14,230 --> 00:06:16,690
It's better if you keep it to yourself.

95
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:20,860
Well look at that.

96
00:06:20,860 --> 00:06:22,820
You can be nice.

97
00:06:27,580 --> 00:06:29,080
Anyway...

98
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:33,920
now the government's got
the two keys it was looking for:

99
00:06:34,460 --> 00:06:37,880
you, who's got the expertise
to awaken the weapon,

100
00:06:38,380 --> 00:06:43,130
and me, who's got the blueprints to build it.

101
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:49,600
And when that power
actually appears in this world,

102
00:06:50,060 --> 00:06:53,520
you can bet the government will
put an end to the Great Pirate Era.

103
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:59,360
Soon, their military might will be unstoppable.
This power will grip the world and rip it apart.

104
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:02,990
That's the threat posed
by these ancient weapons.

105
00:07:03,530 --> 00:07:07,780
Our master didn't lay down his life
protecting the blueprints...

106
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:12,370
for such a pointless future!

107
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:18,500
So, even if I could escape,
it's pointless if it's just me.

108
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:21,960
Somehow, we gotta get you
back to the Straw Hats, too!

109
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:23,210
I can't.

110
00:07:24,130 --> 00:07:27,640
I hurt them just by being with them.

111
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:32,890
But you're not the one hurting them, right?

112
00:07:32,890 --> 00:07:37,270
The government tries to paint
your very existence as a sin,

113
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:43,280
but no matter how dangerous
you may be, you have a right to live.

114
00:07:44,780 --> 00:07:49,910
No matter what kind of ship it is,
the act of building it...

115
00:07:49,910 --> 00:07:52,580
is neither an act of good nor evil!

116
00:07:53,490 --> 00:07:55,540
So...

117
00:07:56,330 --> 00:07:59,000
...her very existence has been a sin.

118
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,380
You're wrong!

119
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:04,420
That you exist is in no way a sin.

120
00:08:15,140 --> 00:08:17,850
Seriously, what happened to your body?

121
00:08:18,310 --> 00:08:20,520
It's covered in scars!

122
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:22,190
Ever since...

123
00:08:22,940 --> 00:08:29,320
that day eight years ago...
when Mr. Tom was taken away...

124
00:08:29,740 --> 00:08:34,660
you've been challenging the sea train.

125
00:08:46,010 --> 00:08:49,430
You wanted to become strong, right?

126
00:08:50,470 --> 00:08:54,560
You didn't want to lose any more loved ones.

127
00:08:54,970 --> 00:08:58,810
You wanted to protect your loved ones!

128
00:09:00,730 --> 00:09:02,150
Yokozuna,

129
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:07,070
now's the time to show us
the result of that training!

130
00:09:09,530 --> 00:09:15,660
Your dear Franky has been
taken away, just like Mr. Tom was.

131
00:09:16,870 --> 00:09:20,500
Right now, this train's following after Franky.

132
00:09:21,580 --> 00:09:24,040
Care to join us?

133
00:09:28,630 --> 00:09:30,130
Straw Hat!

134
00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:33,010
We've got one more friend!

135
00:09:33,010 --> 00:09:34,600
Okay, sounds good!

136
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:38,470
That's our Monster Granny!

137
00:09:38,470 --> 00:09:40,810
Or... are you actually Frog Granny?

138
00:09:40,810 --> 00:09:43,020
Which one is it?

139
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:48,320
Does it really matter?

140
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:51,780
Miss Kokoro! There's a favorable
current at our eight o'clock!

141
00:09:51,780 --> 00:09:53,160
Alright!

142
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:56,330
We've lost quite a bit of time,

143
00:09:56,330 --> 00:09:59,330
but we'll make up for it in a flash!

144
00:09:59,330 --> 00:10:02,160
Let's go, frog!

145
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:09,340
CP9 has arrived!

146
00:10:09,340 --> 00:10:10,550
Hurry up!

147
00:10:11,260 --> 00:10:13,590
Well done on the extended operation, CP9!

148
00:10:13,590 --> 00:10:16,470
Fetch the criminals. They're in car one.

149
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,850
You bastard!

150
00:10:20,850 --> 00:10:23,520
Hands off the goods, dumbass!

151
00:10:20,430 --> 00:10:21,930
Stop it!

152
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:25,860
Do you know who I am?!

153
00:10:26,230 --> 00:10:28,650
Whoa! Don't come this way!

154
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:30,480
Careful! He's a biter!

155
00:10:33,030 --> 00:10:35,240
What an unruly man.

156
00:10:41,950 --> 00:10:43,710
Just like I'd imagine them.

157
00:10:43,710 --> 00:10:45,580
How intimidating.

158
00:10:46,170 --> 00:10:48,710
He's Cutty Flam, right?

159
00:10:48,710 --> 00:10:51,050
Then that woman is...

160
00:10:51,630 --> 00:10:52,760
Nico Robin?!

161
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:54,840
She's gorgeous!

162
00:10:55,430 --> 00:10:57,430
Open the main gate!

163
00:11:17,450 --> 00:11:18,660
Whoa!

164
00:11:18,660 --> 00:11:20,700
What the hell is this place?!

165
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,550
Is this... a waterfall?!

166
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:43,770
I can't see the bottom!

167
00:11:43,770 --> 00:11:46,100
He's so noisy.

168
00:11:51,190 --> 00:11:55,070
Looks like Lucci's group is headed this way...

169
00:11:59,450 --> 00:12:04,750
and they come bearing the best possible gifts.

170
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,330
Well...

171
00:12:08,830 --> 00:12:11,000
today is a joyous occasion.

172
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,130
All eight members of CP9, myself included,

173
00:12:14,130 --> 00:12:17,930
have gathered together in one place
for the first time in five years.

174
00:12:17,930 --> 00:12:20,550
Even so, care to explain this article?!

175
00:12:22,140 --> 00:12:25,220
Your orders were to assassinate
just the three people

176
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:28,480
who lead the local branches
of the Revolutionary Army,

177
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:31,020
but you somehow killed twenty-three of them!

178
00:12:31,020 --> 00:12:33,110
Let's hear your lame excuses!

179
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:39,910
My sincerest apologies, Chief!

180
00:12:39,910 --> 00:12:44,410
The blame should fall...

181
00:12:44,410 --> 00:12:46,290
completely on me!

182
00:12:46,290 --> 00:12:48,040
Stop it, Kumadori!

183
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:50,500
A man shouldn't bow his head so readily!

184
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:54,960
I'll tell the chief what happened, so just sit tight!

185
00:12:56,340 --> 00:12:58,220
Forgive me, Chief!

186
00:12:58,220 --> 00:13:00,430
Now that it has come to this,

187
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:04,140
I will take responsibility and commit seppuku.

188
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:05,560
Don't be a moron!

189
00:13:06,180 --> 00:13:07,600
You've got it wrong, Chief!

190
00:13:07,980 --> 00:13:12,230
We infiltrated them on the designated day
to carry out the assassinations,

191
00:13:12,230 --> 00:13:15,020
but somehow the plans were leaked!

192
00:13:15,020 --> 00:13:18,320
I blabbed in town about the assassination plot!

193
00:13:19,650 --> 00:13:22,870
What?! It was you again, Fukuro?!

194
00:13:22,870 --> 00:13:25,370
What's that zipper on your mouth
even good for?!

195
00:13:25,370 --> 00:13:28,040
You gonna fix these
flapping lips of yours, or what?!

196
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:30,580
We're agents from a covert intelligence unit!

197
00:13:30,580 --> 00:13:32,120
And I went and talked about it!

198
00:13:33,130 --> 00:13:34,750
Don't "cha-pa-pa" me!

199
00:13:36,590 --> 00:13:40,300
Please do not cast blame on Fukuro!

200
00:13:40,670 --> 00:13:45,050
I will take responsibility and commit seppuku.

201
00:13:45,390 --> 00:13:46,680
Iron Body.

202
00:13:48,430 --> 00:13:51,140
How regrettable! I cannot die.

203
00:13:51,140 --> 00:13:54,690
Just die already, you imbecile!

204
00:13:57,520 --> 00:13:59,490
You guys, that's enough.

205
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:04,030
Ouch! I spilled my coffee! Dammit!

206
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:06,740
Also, they said that Nero was useless.

207
00:14:07,330 --> 00:14:08,120
Oh, well.

208
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,580
Hurry!

209
00:14:15,580 --> 00:14:17,840
Can't we go any faster?!

210
00:14:23,220 --> 00:14:28,680
Hey, so that means
Big Bro Franky sacrificed himself?

211
00:14:29,520 --> 00:14:31,680
Yeah, that's right.

212
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:35,270
He tried to save Robin.

213
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:44,320
Our bro is so amazing!

214
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:48,200
If we don't hurry, it'll be too late.

215
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:54,290
Look, guys! It's the lights of
the nightless island, Enies Lobby!

216
00:14:55,710 --> 00:14:57,960
What?! For real? All right!

217
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,960
Let's rescue our bro!

218
00:15:01,710 --> 00:15:02,670
Nightless island?

219
00:15:02,670 --> 00:15:05,720
Yeah. It never becomes night on that island.

220
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:07,220
It's also called a day island.

221
00:15:07,220 --> 00:15:09,810
That's the Judicial Island.

222
00:15:12,310 --> 00:15:13,770
We found them!

223
00:15:14,270 --> 00:15:16,400
Huge king bulls!

224
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:19,270
Ahoy!

225
00:15:22,730 --> 00:15:24,030
– Luffy!
– Luffy!

226
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:27,280
Oh! Sanji!

227
00:15:27,950 --> 00:15:29,830
Who's that?

228
00:15:28,820 --> 00:15:30,950
It's been a while...

229
00:15:30,950 --> 00:15:34,710
It's Mr. Straw Hat!

230
00:15:37,540 --> 00:15:39,960
Seems we met back up without a hitch, huh?

231
00:15:39,960 --> 00:15:43,920
They look ready to march across
the threshold of the World Government!

232
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:46,010
That sounds encouraging!

233
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:54,430
Alright! Enies Lobby is finally within sight!

234
00:15:54,430 --> 00:15:57,690
Let's get ready for the final showdown!

235
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:10,990
– Sogeking from Sniper Island?!
– Sogeking from Sniper Island?!

236
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,450
That's right.

237
00:16:13,450 --> 00:16:15,250
I'm Sir Usopp's best friend.

238
00:16:15,250 --> 00:16:18,460
I'm here because he requested
that I assist you.

239
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:20,420
A h-hero!

240
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:24,000
Since you're wearing a cape,
I thought you might be one.

241
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:26,510
Amazing! I'm meeting a real-life hero!

242
00:16:26,510 --> 00:16:29,640
I see! He's a hero because
he's wearing a cape?

243
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:32,470
That's right! Cape equals hero!

244
00:16:32,470 --> 00:16:33,310
Really?!

245
00:16:33,310 --> 00:16:36,680
Yeah, so if someone is wearing
a cape, they're usually a hero.

246
00:16:33,890 --> 00:16:35,270
Well, if it isn't Usopp.

247
00:16:35,270 --> 00:16:37,640
Usopp! I'm glad he's okay.

248
00:16:37,640 --> 00:16:41,400
That's the long-nosed guy who
marched into the Franky House.

249
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:44,400
That's the long-nosed guy
who got nabbed along with Bro.

250
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:45,690
Sure is.

251
00:16:45,690 --> 00:16:47,110
N-Nice to meet you.

252
00:16:47,110 --> 00:16:48,490
Ah, yes.

253
00:16:48,490 --> 00:16:51,240
That's one of the guys I met at Shift Station.

254
00:16:52,070 --> 00:16:53,990
May I have your autograph?

255
00:16:53,280 --> 00:16:53,990
Sure.

256
00:16:56,290 --> 00:16:57,790
But then...

257
00:16:57,790 --> 00:17:00,000
where did Usopp go?

258
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:03,500
He's fine. You don't have
to worry about him one bit.

259
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:08,970
Anyway, he told me before he departed
to focus all my efforts into rescuing Lady Robin.

260
00:17:08,970 --> 00:17:10,720
Yep. He's right.

261
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:12,140
Wh-Where...?

262
00:17:12,140 --> 00:17:14,350
Where is this Sniper Island?

263
00:17:14,350 --> 00:17:15,760
Well...

264
00:17:16,140 --> 00:17:17,220
it's...

265
00:17:17,220 --> 00:17:20,560
♪ Sniper Island's favorite son... ♪

266
00:17:21,770 --> 00:17:22,980
...in your...

267
00:17:23,810 --> 00:17:25,190
hearts.

268
00:17:26,650 --> 00:17:29,360
♪ Evildoers... ♪

269
00:17:27,610 --> 00:17:28,900
Our hearts!

270
00:17:30,240 --> 00:17:33,870
♪ better run... ♪

271
00:17:33,870 --> 00:17:34,660
Where exactly?!

272
00:17:34,660 --> 00:17:38,450
– ♪ Sniper Island's favorite son... ♪
– ♪ Sniper Island's favorite son... ♪

273
00:17:38,450 --> 00:17:41,080
♪ Evildoers better run... ♪

274
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:41,790
Go!

275
00:17:41,790 --> 00:17:44,790
– ♪ Evildoers better run... ♪
– ♪ Evildoers better run... ♪

276
00:17:44,790 --> 00:17:45,630
Go!

277
00:17:45,630 --> 00:17:46,840
♪ My aim... ♪

278
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:47,340
Go!

279
00:17:47,340 --> 00:17:49,050
– ♪ My aim... ♪
– ♪ My aim... ♪

280
00:17:49,050 --> 00:17:49,590
♪ ...is always... ♪

281
00:17:49,590 --> 00:17:49,970
Go!

282
00:17:49,970 --> 00:17:50,760
– ♪ ...is always... ♪
– ♪ ...is always... ♪

283
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:51,220
♪ ...true! ♪

284
00:17:51,220 --> 00:17:51,550
Go!

285
00:17:51,550 --> 00:17:52,180
– ♪ ...true! ♪
– ♪ ...true! ♪

286
00:17:44,590 --> 00:17:45,250
Nami.

287
00:17:45,250 --> 00:17:46,500
Huh?

288
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,170
What is it, Sanji?

289
00:17:49,340 --> 00:17:52,180
And all you idiots here with Nami...

290
00:17:52,180 --> 00:17:52,680
Huh?

291
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:56,260
...before we rescue Robin,
there's something you need to know.

292
00:18:03,650 --> 00:18:05,020
That's how it is.

293
00:18:05,020 --> 00:18:09,610
CP9 is exploiting a vulnerability
from Robin's past.

294
00:18:10,190 --> 00:18:12,990
I'm not saying we shouldn't bring her back.

295
00:18:13,530 --> 00:18:16,280
But even if we march into enemy territory,

296
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:19,950
there's no guarantee
Robin will let us help her.

297
00:18:21,460 --> 00:18:23,620
None of that matters!

298
00:18:23,620 --> 00:18:26,630
I'm not gonna stand for this!

299
00:18:28,130 --> 00:18:29,090
Robin, you suck!

300
00:18:29,090 --> 00:18:30,670
Why say that?!

301
00:18:31,010 --> 00:18:32,510
Of course I'd say it!

302
00:18:32,510 --> 00:18:35,050
Why the hell wouldn't
she want us to rescue her?!

303
00:18:35,430 --> 00:18:39,430
She can't bear the thought of what might
happen to us after we rescue her!

304
00:18:39,430 --> 00:18:40,970
Who cares about that?!

305
00:18:41,390 --> 00:18:43,770
If we do nothing, she'll be killed, right?!

306
00:18:43,770 --> 00:18:46,230
There's no way she wants to die,
so we'll rescue her!

307
00:18:46,690 --> 00:18:48,940
That may be true, but...

308
00:18:48,940 --> 00:18:50,070
Give it a rest.

309
00:18:50,070 --> 00:18:52,940
Either way, there's no changing course.

310
00:18:53,530 --> 00:18:54,990
We'll just rescue her.

311
00:18:54,990 --> 00:18:57,570
We'll bring down the whole place!

312
00:18:58,160 --> 00:19:00,540
And there's a new move I wanna try!

313
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:08,000
Guys, take a look at this.

314
00:19:08,340 --> 00:19:12,170
Some time ago, I went to Enies Lobby
for railway maintenance.

315
00:19:12,510 --> 00:19:15,010
I drew everything I could remember about it.

316
00:19:15,590 --> 00:19:18,260
This is a rough sketch of Enies Lobby.

317
00:19:23,850 --> 00:19:29,310
The Gates of Justice at the back of the island
are only accessible through the Tower of Justice.

318
00:19:29,310 --> 00:19:31,690
What's all this? What's this dark area?

319
00:19:31,690 --> 00:19:33,490
It indicates a waterfall.

320
00:19:33,490 --> 00:19:34,820
A waterfall?

321
00:19:34,820 --> 00:19:36,990
Well, you'll see once you're in there.

322
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:40,700
If we can't recover Nico Robin
and Franky somewhere on this path

323
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:44,660
between the main gate
to the Gates of Justice, then we fail.

324
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,160
Why?!

325
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:50,210
No matter where they take Robin,
we'll just follow them until we get her back!

326
00:19:50,210 --> 00:19:53,000
Didn't I explain this
before we left Water Seven?!

327
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:57,880
The only destinations beyond those gates are
Marine Headquarters and the undersea prison.

328
00:19:58,260 --> 00:20:02,560
We'll need to settle this matter
before they reach them, no matter what.

329
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:04,560
She's right.

330
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:08,100
Still, even if we all rush in,

331
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:11,820
if we encounter CP9, the only ones
who can hope to beat them...

332
00:20:11,820 --> 00:20:13,480
is you guys.

333
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:17,150
Our time on this train has shown me
just how strong you guys are.

334
00:20:17,150 --> 00:20:20,490
So, you guys wait here
on the sea for five minutes,

335
00:20:20,490 --> 00:20:24,120
then charge through the island's
main gate in Rocketman.

336
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:28,330
We'll go in first to bust open
the main gate and the island gate.

337
00:20:28,330 --> 00:20:30,710
That way, the train can pass through.

338
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:36,590
After that, you'll need to keep moving forward,
no matter how many of us fall.

339
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:41,220
We have just over sixty people,

340
00:20:41,220 --> 00:20:44,560
but our enemy's forces are probably
well above 2,000 or even 3,000.

341
00:20:45,430 --> 00:20:50,980
We'd like you guys to only go after CP9
and avoid any unnecessary battles.

342
00:20:50,980 --> 00:20:52,980
Okay, got it.

343
00:20:52,980 --> 00:20:54,480
Okay, guys!

344
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:57,150
We just arrived in front of the island!

345
00:20:57,150 --> 00:21:01,070
Take a good look at the sky
behind Enies Lobby.

346
00:21:02,530 --> 00:21:04,910
Those are the Gates of Justice.

347
00:21:04,910 --> 00:21:10,830
– Whoooa! They're huuuge!
– Whoooa! They're huuuge!

348
00:21:13,750 --> 00:21:16,800
They never open all the way.

349
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:21,840
When criminals are taken through them,
they open just a crack.

350
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:26,180
Behind those doors is a nest of
giant sea kings just like in the Calm Belt,

351
00:21:26,180 --> 00:21:30,190
the areas of sea that run along
both sides of the Grand Line.

352
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:33,400
So no ordinary ships venture in there.

353
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:35,770
I don't know how,

354
00:21:35,770 --> 00:21:39,820
but the Marines have a way to pass
through the gates without being harmed.

355
00:21:39,820 --> 00:21:43,620
In other words, just like the pirate girl said,

356
00:21:43,620 --> 00:21:46,660
if you want to rescue a criminal
who's been brought here,

357
00:21:46,660 --> 00:21:50,410
you've got until the moment
before they go through those gates to do it!

358
00:21:50,410 --> 00:21:53,460
Now, there's no time to lose!

359
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:58,670
All right! As planned, we're gonna go in first!

360
00:21:59,510 --> 00:22:01,510
We'll cover your entrance!

361
00:22:01,510 --> 00:22:04,720
Hey, you two! Aren't you
supposed to be with us?!

362
00:22:10,180 --> 00:22:11,890
Oh? Where's Luffy?

363
00:22:11,890 --> 00:22:14,520
Huh? He was right here a second ago.

364
00:22:20,690 --> 00:22:21,950
Is that Mr. Straw Hat?

365
00:22:21,950 --> 00:22:23,530
What?!

366
00:22:26,870 --> 00:22:29,330
– What?!
– What?!

367
00:22:29,330 --> 00:22:32,660
Why the hell is he doing things on his own?!

368
00:22:32,660 --> 00:22:35,460
That guy didn't get the plan at all!

369
00:22:37,210 --> 00:22:38,960
So much for that...

370
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:40,920
He said "got it," didn't he?

371
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:43,550
It's impossible for him to wait five minutes.

372
00:22:43,550 --> 00:22:45,140
We should've known.

373
00:22:46,970 --> 00:22:49,810
What an impatient guy!

374
00:22:49,810 --> 00:22:52,230
Go! Pirate guy!

375
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:59,360
Sodom and Gomorrah, don't fall behind!

376
00:22:59,360 --> 00:23:03,030
Climb up the iron fence
and break open the main gate!

377
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:09,620
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

378
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:12,450
Gum-Gum...

379
00:23:12,450 --> 00:23:15,040
Rocket!

380
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:17,080
What was that...?

381
00:23:18,960 --> 00:23:20,210
Something just flew by!

382
00:23:24,470 --> 00:23:26,050
What is this place?!

383
00:23:26,050 --> 00:23:27,720
What a huge hole!

384
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:29,760
It looks like the island is floating.

385
00:23:31,310 --> 00:23:32,770
There's someone up there!

386
00:23:32,770 --> 00:23:35,230
It's an intruder! Shoot him down!

387
00:23:35,940 --> 00:23:37,730
They found me.

388
00:23:40,730 --> 00:23:42,610
He went past the gate!

389
00:23:47,990 --> 00:23:50,280
This is the main gate! This is the main gate!

390
00:23:50,280 --> 00:23:52,580
Reporting to the chief and the island gate!

391
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:55,830
This is the main gate! Do you copy?!

392
00:23:57,170 --> 00:23:59,330
What is it? What's going on?

393
00:23:59,710 --> 00:24:04,050
An intruder climbed over the main gate
and is rapidly approaching the island gate!

394
00:24:04,050 --> 00:24:07,720
So it's just one intruder.
Calm down and take care of him.

395
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:08,510
So it's just one intruder.
Calm down and take care of him.

396
00:24:08,510 --> 00:24:10,600
Yes, but...

397
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:12,510
This is the island gate.

398
00:24:12,510 --> 00:24:14,100
We have eyes on the intruder.

399
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:16,730
We'll take care of him right away, rest assured.

400
00:24:19,150 --> 00:24:21,730
Hey, kid. Stop this already.

401
00:24:21,730 --> 00:24:23,690
Do you know what this place is?

402
00:24:23,690 --> 00:24:25,610
Do not take him lightly!

403
00:24:25,610 --> 00:24:27,860
Either my eyes deceive me, or that man is...

404
00:24:29,910 --> 00:24:31,620
Straw Hat Luffy!

405
00:24:37,410 --> 00:24:39,540
What?! Can you confirm what you just said?!

406
00:24:39,540 --> 00:24:41,210
I think it's Straw Hat...

407
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:46,260
a pirate with a 100-million-berry
bounty on his head!

408
00:24:51,430 --> 00:24:52,760
Where's Robin?!

409
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:12,240
Where the hell is Robin?!

